<subSubSection id="E8CD8C7B9356DC4B73247524BB09D0D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="465" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CF5A78A37CC8148D81C91F1DAB5861A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="465">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="01EA996002DE31B88A7FA796642D9FE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis id="6CEDE29030FECFDD0CB599208498FC90" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="465">Nymph.</emphasis>
See genus diagnosis. Otherwise, if more species are discovered, specific differences in shape of labial and maxillary palps, and in setation of the legs are expected. Species with less derived characters (setation of pedicellus, shape of mentum) may also be expected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AC4E61D3B37F41D321A1715C99605D5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="465" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="88AE34439ACAE66CAC81A863B8CF68BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="465">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="53D0655AC31BF0CAFDDD23EC3A83A5C6" pageId="0" pageNumber="465">Madagasikara is the Malagasy name of Madagascar.</paragraph>
